Jason is there said in after life to have been driven from Thessaly by the daughters of Pelias, to have been reconciled to Medea, to have reinstated Aeetes, whom he found in exile, to have gained great victories‚ and assigned a territory from his conquests to his fol- lowers from Greece. The Albani, ac- cording to Justin, gave to Cn. Pompeius a different account of themselves, and claimed the favour of Rome as having had their home on the Alban Mount, and having followed Heracles from Italy to the East. The real origin of both nations appears to be Scythic‚ and the Albani have been thought to be the same as the Alauni or Alani.
